{
  "stem": "15197.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was the one also who was responsible together with the young people there-- Marek Edelman, who is now in Warsaw still alive, Dr.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Edelman, and Michal Klepfisz-- responsible for organizing the four Bund youth groups in the fighter's organization.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were also the representative together and meet with Mordechaj Anielewicz from Hashomer Hatzair-- they had four groups.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They meet with representative from other youth groups.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this is how they started to work to coordinate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The first really response of the organized armed resistance took place the 18th of January, 1943.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But this was not too much organized yet.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I would not say that it was very successful.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But this was the first attempt.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And after it they came to the conclusion that they have to separate the youth groups.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They have to live constantly together to be ready in case of need to be in an organized way to step and to stand up.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And mine assignments were, if I could get and I got ones, a few kilo of dynamite to smuggle this into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Usually I had a code number by telephone from the working shops in the ghetto and from other youth which was staying near the telephone.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we used to give our code and to decide at what point we will smuggle over dynamite or guns or things.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And this is how I got more and more involved.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I used to come in into the ghetto as a smuggler and bringing in something like bottle or something, different things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But the bottle was just the paper and inside was the dynamite.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And to smuggle out sometimes jewelry to change it there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By this time the underground knew more about gas chambers, yes.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
